To see Spain brought so low,

256
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:42,036
with an enemy thriving within her borders,
feasting on her strength.

257
00:36:42,120 --> 00:36:44,759
The shame is too much.
I've failed her.

258
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:47,115
Dare not pity Spain.

259
00:36:49,320 --> 00:36:51,880
These times are dark,

260
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:57,034
but every shadow, no matter how deep,
is threatened by morning light.

261
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:59,236
Of course.

262
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:01,629
This loyalty of yours

263
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:05,110
inspires you to protect Spain at any cost,

264
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:09,478
but killing the inquisitor is suicide.

265
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:12,835
Europe would have my head.

266
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:17,913
I, for one, am not ready to die yet.
Are you?

267
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:20,468
I will die for Spain.

268
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:24,875
I know, Conquistador.

269
00:37:24,960 --> 00:37:26,473
I know.

270
00:37:26,560 --> 00:37:30,439
And this bravery of yours,
it may save us yet.

271
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:34,757
For Spain has a plan.

272
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:37,832
There is hope.

273
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:40,354
- There's hope?
- Father.

274
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:02,989
I am Father Avila
of her royal Franciscan order.

275
00:38:03,080 --> 00:38:05,548
Our allegiance remains with Spain.

276
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:07,473
Father.

277
00:38:07,560 --> 00:38:10,074
Guards, leave us.

278
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:15,998
Conquistador,

279
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:21,837
I am going to tell you the true reason
why the inquisitor pits cross against crown.

280
00:38:22,840 --> 00:38:27,960
One year ago, Father Avila returned
from the jungles of New Spain

281
00:38:28,040 --> 00:38:30,031
with a secret so great,

282
00:38:30,120 --> 00:38:33,556
it promised to free
all mankind from tyranny.

283
00:38:33,640 --> 00:38:37,474
Spain desired this treasure
above all things,

284
00:38:37,560 --> 00:38:40,711
but the inquisitor feared it
with equal measure.

285
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:43,394
When I refused to give up my quest for it,

286
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:48,235
he responded with this violent coup
to bring Spain to her knees.

287
00:38:48,320 --> 00:38:51,039
But we have not yielded,

288
00:38:51,120 --> 00:38:53,873
and now we will defeat him.

289
00:39:01,640 --> 00:39:04,757
This is our hope.

290
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:08,628
- A dagger?
- Used in religious rituals.

291
00:39:08,720 --> 00:39:11,393
I took it from a dead Mayan priest.

292
00:39:14,240 --> 00:39:16,310
The marking on the hilt...

293
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:20,873
Do you see it?

294
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:28,631
It is a map.

295
00:39:29,320 --> 00:39:32,756
A map to the Mayans' greatest secret.

296
00:39:32,840 --> 00:39:37,994
Greater than Chichen ltzá, greater than
Yaxchilán, greater even than Tikal.

297
00:39:38,080 --> 00:39:42,870
Here, in the centre, in the core
of the once-great Mayan civilisation,

298
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:47,112
we will find a lost pyramid.

299
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:50,429
No.

300
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:52,238
Not lost.

301
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:57,553
Hidden.
The hidden pyramid of the Mayan myths.

302
00:39:57,640 --> 00:40:01,076
The myths tell us of a holy pyramid,

303
00:40:01,160 --> 00:40:03,799
built upon the navel of the Earth,

304
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:06,713
the birthplace of life.

305
00:40:07,720 --> 00:40:10,234
A special tree sprouts there.

306
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:15,393
They say whoever drinks of its sap

307
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:18,392
will live forever.

308
00:40:19,840 --> 00:40:21,990
Eternal life?

309
00:40:23,080 --> 00:40:27,471
Spain hangs at the whims of a merciless
enemy and you taunt us with yarns?

310
00:40:27,560 --> 00:40:29,949
They are not yarns.

311
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:33,235
Remember,

312
00:40:33,320 --> 00:40:35,515
our own Bible confirms it.

313
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:39,354
In Genesis, there are two trees
in the Garden of Eden -

314
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:43,149
the Tree of Knowledge
and the Tree of Life.

315
00:40:43,240 --> 00:40:46,357
When Adam and Eve disobeyed the Lord
and ate from the Tree of Knowledge,

316
00:40:46,440 --> 00:40:50,149
the Lord banned them from the garden
and hid the Tree of Life.

317
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:22,911
Could it be?

318
00:41:27,840 --> 00:41:29,398
Could it be?

319
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:33,149
Kneel, Conquistador.

320
00:41:38,240 --> 00:41:40,913
Let in the morning light.

321
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:59,830
The beast runs amok in my kingdom.

322
00:42:00,800 --> 00:42:03,598
He has isolated me,

323
00:42:03,680 --> 00:42:08,549
and now he is sharpening his talons
for one more fateful push.

324
00:42:09,680 --> 00:42:13,434
But salvation lies
in the jungles of New Spain.

325
00:42:29,720 --> 00:42:32,632
Will you deliver Spain from bondage?

326
00:42:32,720 --> 00:42:35,518
Upon my honour and my life.

327
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:49,996
Then you shall take this ring
to remind you of your promise.

328
00:42:52,880 --> 00:42:56,111
You shall wear it when you find Eden,

329
00:42:56,200 --> 00:42:58,509
and when you return,

330
00:42:58,600 --> 00:43:00,750
I shall be your Eve.

331
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:06,678
Together, we will live forever.

332
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:24,511
Iz?

333
00:43:27,120 --> 00:43:28,872
Lzzi?

334
00:43:53,200 --> 00:43:55,998
- There you are.
- Hey, what are you doing here?

335
00:43:56,080 --> 00:44:00,756
- Babe, we have Lipper at three.
- This is an actual Mayan book.

336
00:44:00,840 --> 00:44:05,960
Look. It explains their creation myth. You see,
that's First Father. He's the very first human.

337
00:44:06,040 --> 00:44:08,235
Is he dead?

338
00:44:08,320 --> 00:44:11,756
He sacrificed himself to make the world.

339
00:44:12,360 --> 00:44:15,238
- The Tree of Life's bursting out of his belly.
- Come on.

340
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:20,997
Listen. His body became the tree's roots.
They spread and formed the Earth.

341
00:44:21,080 --> 00:44:24,709
His soul became the branches,
rising up, forming the sky.

342
00:44:24,800 --> 00:44:27,234
All that remained
was First Father's head.

343
00:44:27,320 --> 00:44:31,074
His children hung it in the heavens,
creating Xibalba.

344
00:44:31,160 --> 00:44:33,469
Xibalba? The star.

345
00:44:33,560 --> 00:44:35,630
Nebula.

346
00:44:35,720 --> 00:44:38,154
- So what do you think?
- About?

347
00:44:38,240 --> 00:44:40,117
That idea.

348
00:44:40,200 --> 00:44:43,078
Death as an act of creation.

349
00:44:45,760 --> 00:44:47,876
Stay together, guys.

350
00:44:48,840 --> 00:44:52,355
I'll pull out the car
and meet you in front.

351
00:45:14,200 --> 00:45:16,156
Iz. Iz!

352
00:45:40,240 --> 00:45:42,435
- Tommy.
- Hey.

353
00:45:44,040 --> 00:45:45,712
Tommy.

354
00:45:52,240 --> 00:45:54,674
You're all right.

355
00:45:56,400 --> 00:45:58,789
- I'm close.
- No.

356
00:45:58,880 --> 00:46:00,552
There are options.

357
00:46:00,640 --> 00:46:04,315
- We'll have to make some choices.
- Alan?

358
00:46:06,400 --> 00:46:11,235
You had a minor seizure. The growth in
your brainstem's back and it's growing faster.

359
00:46:11,320 --> 00:46:13,470
- The next time...
- No!

360
00:46:14,440 --> 00:46:15,998
No.

361
00:46:16,080 --> 00:46:18,036
We had a breakthrough.

362
00:46:18,120 --> 00:46:20,873
I know I can translate it to help you.

363
00:46:20,960 --> 00:46:23,235
I just need a little more time, OK?

364
00:46:23,320 --> 00:46:26,471
There's hope.
There's real hope.

365
00:46:26,560 --> 00:46:29,552
- Tommy.
- What? What, baby?

366
00:46:33,840 --> 00:46:36,638
- I wasn't afraid.
- I know.

367
00:46:36,720 --> 00:46:39,234
You're very strong.

368
00:46:39,320 --> 00:46:41,072
No.

369
00:46:42,280 --> 00:46:45,158
- No.
- What?

370
00:46:45,240 --> 00:46:47,549
When I fell

371
00:46:49,400 --> 00:46:51,709
I was full.

372
00:46:54,040 --> 00:46:55,951
Held.

373
00:46:57,840 --> 00:47:00,673
I know.
I caught you. I held you.

374
00:47:07,040 --> 00:47:11,033
It's OK, lz.
Everything's gonna be all right.

375
00:47:19,000 --> 00:47:21,036
There's time.
We have time.

376
00:47:50,000 --> 00:47:52,514
We need to examine
the hippocampal region.

377
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:56,479
- What the hell's going on?
- I brought in Dean Katari and Dr...

378
00:47:56,560 --> 00:47:58,357
I'm sorry, what are you doing here?

379
00:47:59,640 --> 00:48:05,078
- Antonio and Betty were just showing me...
- Donovan's synaptic growth increased.

380
00:48:05,160 --> 00:48:08,311
His brain is identical to scans
from 12 years ago, when he was six.

381
00:48:08,920 --> 00:48:11,195
And the tumour?

382
00:48:15,440 --> 00:48:17,590
- Exactly. Please?
- Tommy...

383
00:48:17,680 --> 00:48:19,989
Please!

384
00:48:20,080 --> 00:48:24,790
Perhaps you should wait for me in my office.
Manny. I'll be right there.

385
00:48:24,880 --> 00:48:28,509
- Thomas, I'd like a word with you in private.
- After surgery.

386
00:48:40,320 --> 00:48:42,072
First cut.

387
00:48:44,760 --> 00:48:47,672
Tommy.
Dr Lipperjust called.

388
00:48:47,760 --> 00:48:53,517
He said lzzi's doing better and they're gonna
move her to a regular floor in the morning.

389
00:49:07,280 --> 00:49:10,875
When we're done here,
I want you to prep Cain.

390
00:49:15,560 --> 00:49:18,552
I'll get her.
She'll take care of it.

391
00:49:37,440 --> 00:49:40,238
What do you think you're doing?

392
00:49:40,320 --> 00:49:44,677
You don't abandon results like that.
You repeat the procedure, get a confirmation.

393
00:49:44,760 --> 00:49:50,039
Confirmation that the tumour's unaffected?
She'll be dead by then.

394
00:49:50,120 --> 00:49:52,031
Tommy.

395
00:49:55,480 --> 00:49:57,232
She had a seizure.

396
00:50:00,360 --> 00:50:02,669
I'm so sorry.

397
00:50:04,520 --> 00:50:06,750
- How's she doing?
- She's stable.

398
00:50:08,120 --> 00:50:10,031
Who's with her?

399
00:50:11,280 --> 00:50:13,794
- She's alone?
- She needs to rest.

400
00:50:13,880 --> 00:50:18,590
No one invents new drugs overnight. No one!
You're not being rational.

401
00:50:18,680 --> 00:50:21,513
- You can't fix everything!
- Don't tell me what I can do.

402
00:50:21,600 --> 00:50:27,550
- Your wife needs you. Why are you here?
- Why the fuck do you think I'm here?

403
00:50:35,920 --> 00:50:37,831
Shit.

404
00:51:40,480 --> 00:51:42,596
I'll leave you two alone.

405
00:51:44,080 --> 00:51:47,038
Lilly, I'm sorry about before.

406
00:51:49,880 --> 00:51:51,871
She's amazing.

407
00:51:54,560 --> 00:51:56,471
Lillian,

408
00:51:56,560 --> 00:51:59,120
could...

409
00:51:59,200 --> 00:52:03,034
could you have Henry
re-scan the animals for me?

410
00:52:03,120 --> 00:52:05,270
- OK.
- Thanks.

411
00:52:08,120 --> 00:52:10,031
- Hey.
- Hey.

412
00:52:11,800 --> 00:52:15,759
I brought your manuscript
in case you want to work.

413
00:52:20,960 --> 00:52:22,996
How are you feeling?

414
00:52:23,080 --> 00:52:24,718
Good.

415
00:52:28,840 --> 00:52:30,751
I'm sorry.

416
00:52:33,760 --> 00:52:35,716
What about?

417
00:52:43,280 --> 00:52:45,350
There's been progress at work.

418
00:52:47,440 --> 00:52:51,353
My conquistador.
Always conquering.

419
00:52:51,440 --> 00:52:55,797
- No. Something amazing. We tested...
- That's for you.

420
00:52:56,680 --> 00:52:59,274
It's for me? What is it?

421
00:52:59,360 --> 00:53:01,316
Open it.

422
00:53:21,800 --> 00:53:24,268
Pen and ink. For writing.

423
00:53:32,080 --> 00:53:35,390
It's all done except the last chapter.

424
00:53:37,240 --> 00:53:39,151
I want you to help me.

425
00:53:40,240 --> 00:53:42,310
How?

426
00:53:42,400 --> 00:53:44,516
Finish it.

427
00:53:47,200 --> 00:53:48,997
Finish it.

428
00:53:49,080 --> 00:53:51,640
- I don't know how it ends.
- You do.

429
00:53:52,560 --> 00:53:54,755
You will.

430
00:53:54,840 --> 00:53:56,751
Stop.

431
00:54:02,200 --> 00:54:05,476
- Remember Moses Morales?
- Who?

432
00:54:06,920 --> 00:54:10,151
- The Mayan guide I told you about.
- From your trip?

433
00:54:11,360 --> 00:54:15,353
The last night I was with him,
he told me about his father who had died.

434
00:54:15,440 --> 00:54:17,396
- But Moses wouldn't believe it.
- Izzi!

435
00:54:17,480 --> 00:54:20,870
No, no. Listen. Listen.

436
00:54:20,960 --> 00:54:24,430
He said if they dug his father's body up,

437
00:54:25,640 --> 00:54:27,551
he would be gone.

438
00:54:28,800 --> 00:54:31,917
They'd planted a seed over his grave.

439
00:54:32,000 --> 00:54:33,911
The seed became a tree.

440
00:54:35,440 --> 00:54:39,513
Moses said his father became part of that tree.

441
00:54:39,600 --> 00:54:43,752
He grew into the wood, into the bloom.

442
00:54:46,560 --> 00:54:49,791
And when a sparrow ate the tree's fruit,

443
00:54:50,640 --> 00:54:53,154
his father flew with the birds.

444
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:56,911
He said

445
00:54:59,040 --> 00:55:01,793
death was his father's road to awe.

446
00:55:04,360 --> 00:55:06,351
That's what he called it.

447
00:55:07,520 --> 00:55:09,397
The road to awe.

448
00:55:11,240 --> 00:55:13,515
Now,

449
00:55:13,600 --> 00:55:17,957
I've been trying to write the last chapter and
I haven't been able to get that out of my head.

450
00:55:18,040 --> 00:55:20,315
Why are you telling me this?

451
00:55:21,200 --> 00:55:23,714
I'm not afraid any more, Tommy.

452
00:55:34,800 --> 00:55:39,396
I asked Lilly if I could be buried at her farm.

453
00:55:39,480 --> 00:55:41,789
No, stop it!

454
00:55:44,040 --> 00:55:48,113
- I want you to be with me.
- I am with you. Look.

455
00:55:49,280 --> 00:55:51,475
I'll always be with you.

456
00:55:53,960 --> 00:55:55,518
I promise.

457
00:56:00,320 --> 00:56:03,198
Will you stay with me tonight?

458
00:56:04,920 --> 00:56:07,229
Yeah. I'll stay.

459
00:56:14,680 --> 00:56:16,591
I'll stay.

460
00:57:04,480 --> 00:57:06,118
Don't worry,

461
00:57:06,880 --> 00:57:08,791
we're almost there.

462
00:57:13,120 --> 00:57:16,430
Through that last dark cloud is a dying star.

463
00:57:19,920 --> 00:57:22,992
And soon enough, Xibalba will die.

464
00:57:24,600 --> 00:57:27,717
And when it explodes,
you will be reborn.

465
00:57:30,000 --> 00:57:31,911
You will bloom.

466
00:57:37,960 --> 00:57:39,951
And I will live.

467
00:58:09,040 --> 00:58:11,713
Don't worry.
We're almost there.

468
01:00:54,440 --> 01:00:58,035
Thank you, Lord! We are here!

469
01:01:00,840 --> 01:01:02,751
Circles.

470
01:01:03,920 --> 01:01:05,990
He leads us in circles.

471
01:01:07,720 --> 01:01:11,030
Only we are left.
All of your countrymen are dead.

472
01:01:11,120 --> 01:01:14,795
He killed them all with this blind quest.

473
01:01:17,680 --> 01:01:20,558
It's time. Time to stop him.

474
01:01:41,080 --> 01:01:43,992
Captain, we are lost.

475
01:01:44,080 --> 01:01:47,834
The Franciscan and his tales are false.

476
01:01:47,920 --> 01:01:50,070
There is no hope for us here.

477
01:01:51,600 --> 01:01:53,511
There's only death.

478
01:01:54,440 --> 01:01:58,752
- I've mapped us a course back to the ships.
- Coward.

479
01:01:59,520 --> 01:02:01,317
Damn the maps!

480
01:02:05,920 --> 01:02:08,275
We're close and I will find it.

481
01:02:08,360 --> 01:02:11,318
Captain! Captain! Captain!

482
01:02:11,400 --> 01:02:14,153
Father. What is it, Franciscan?

483
01:02:15,080 --> 01:02:17,071
In the jungle...

484
01:02:17,160 --> 01:02:19,310
The marking on the hilt.

485
01:02:19,400 --> 01:02:23,279
- On the dagger?
- It is the same. The same as on the stone.

486
01:02:42,920 --> 01:02:47,357
Your choice - die now
or, by my side, fight and live.

487
01:02:58,800 --> 01:03:02,270
- You fool.
- Captain!

488
01:03:02,360 --> 01:03:04,351
Father.

489
01:03:04,440 --> 01:03:06,635
Take it.

490
01:03:06,720 --> 01:03:08,392
We are here.

491
01:03:08,480 --> 01:03:10,675
- Where?
- The temple is there.

492
01:03:16,400 --> 01:03:18,231
Sorry, Father.

493
01:03:19,400 --> 01:03:21,868
For you, there is only death.

494
01:03:23,200 --> 01:03:25,998
But our destiny is life.

495
01:03:51,320 --> 01:03:54,471
You shall wear it when you find Eden,

496
01:03:54,560 --> 01:03:58,838
and when you return,
I shall be your Eve.

497
01:04:08,760 --> 01:04:10,751
Iz! Lz!

498
01:04:16,560 --> 01:04:18,630
Come on, come on, come on!

499
01:04:18,720 --> 01:04:20,836
Oh, no. Please! Please!

500
01:04:23,400 --> 01:04:25,789
- Step aside.
